title: Paappi Appachaa
subTitle: Paappi, a mischievous man, is in love with his childhood sweetheart, Annie. His relationship with his father turns sour after he thrashes Annie's prospective groom.

title: Mudhugavu
subTitle: Bharath, a technical student, has a strange habit that causes trouble for him and the people around him on several occasions.

title: Gauthamante Radham
subTitle: Gauthaman's joy is palpable after securing his driving licence, as he dreams of driving the very first car his family has ever possessed.

title: Captain
subTitle: Kannayiram, a powerful gangster, kills Ramasamy, for not giving up his land to him. After hearing this news, Shiva, Ramasamy's brother, flees the military camp to avenge his brother's death.

title: Oru Yamandan Premakadha
subTitle: Lallu, a happy-go-lucky person who loves to hang out with his friends, is in pursuit of true love. One day, he finds a photo of a missing woman, Diya, in the newspaper and feels a spark.

title: Rappakal
subTitle: Saraswathiyamma is the head of a noble family that treats her servant Krishnan as one of her own sons. When her relatives conspire to sell her house, she and Krishnan set out to save it.

title: Lucifer
subTitle: The demise of the leader of a political party leads to a massive power struggle. Amidst the chaos, a mystical man named Stephen comes in to ascend the throne.

title: Thondimuthalum Driksakshiyum
subTitle: Newly-weds Sreeja and Prasad struggle to cope with their lives and decide to sell Sreeja's gold chain for money. However, a thief steals the chain during a bus journey, adding to their woes.

title: Drishyam 2
subTitle: Georgekutty, a cinema hall owner, is a changed man who thrives in life. However, when his family become entangled in a criminal investigation, he must protect them from the legal institution.

title: Udhaharanam Sujatha
subTitle: Sujatha, a single mother who struggles to make ends meet, is disappointed when her daughter Athira decides to drop out of school. So Sujatha devises a plan to motivate her to study.

title: Udhaharanam Sujatha
subTitle: Sujatha, a single mother who struggles to make ends meet, is disappointed when her daughter Athira decides to drop out of school. So Sujatha devises a plan to motivate her to study.

title: Ben Johnson
subTitle: Johnson, the honourable son of a dreaded local thug, decides to erase the bad image of his father in the society. He becomes a police officer and fights to bring criminals to justice.

title: Thelivu
subTitle: Gauri accidentally kills a wealthy businessman to stop him from molesting a little girl. When his minions chase after her and her husband, they must hide until the proof to exonerate them is found.

title: Chess
subTitle: A man murders his rich brother-in-law with the help of three co-conspirators to amass his wealth. He also manages to discredit the deceased man's illegitimate son.

title: Naran
subTitle: Velayudhan, an orphan, is loved by the villagers as he keeps the village free from unsavoury people and practices. However, an evil moneylender and politician get jealous and try to get rid of him.

title: The Priest
subTitle: Father Carmen, a priest, joins hands with the police to investigate a series of mysterious suicides. However, he soon stumbles upon a disturbing fact that has serious consequences.

title: Swarna Kaduva
subTitle: Rini, the right-hand of a corrupt businessman, begins to become greedy for money. He asks his boss to help him settle down with a jewellery shop, but fate has other plans for him.

title: Kilometers and Kilometers
subTitle: A poor tour guide from Kerala takes an American client on a journey through India. During their travels, the changing landscapes and experiences help them reshape their understanding of each other.

title: Guruvayur Ambalanadayil
subTitle: A young man eagerly awaits his wedding, but fate twists cruelly, forcing him into a lifelong bond with a woman who harbours nothing but resentment for him.

title: Traffic
subTitle: Travelling from Mumbai to Pune in a four-wheeler, a motley crew of unlikely heroes must race against time to deliver a heart to a 13-year-old patient.

title: Traffic
subTitle: Travelling from Mumbai to Pune in a four-wheeler, a motley crew of unlikely heroes must race against time to deliver a heart to a 13-year-old patient.

title: Poomaram
subTitle: Two colleges participate in a youth festival. Gauthaman represents Maharaja college whereas Irene represents all-time winners, St Teresa's College.

title: Memories
subTitle: Sam Alex, a police officer, resorts to alcohol to ease the pain of his family's death. However, his life turns around when he is called to investigate a series of murders showing a similar pattern.

title: Sudani From Nigeria
subTitle: Majeed, a football coach in Malappuram, recuits Nigerian players for his local team. When star player Samuel is injured, he stays with Majeed, leading to a deep bond despite cultural differences.

title: Porinju Mariam Jose
subTitle: Porinju and Mariam, two lovers who share a complicated past, and Jose, their mutual friend, become involved in a life-changing village feud.

title: The King & The Commissioner
subTitle: Joseph Alex and Bharathchandran, two police officers, try to prevent Major Abu Jalal Rana, a terrorist, from attacking New Delhi.

title: Ponman
subTitle: Ajesh, a gold dealer, lends some gold jewelry for a village wedding, unaware of the betrayal ahead. However, the bride's husband plans to keep the gold and kill Ajesh.

title: Kilichundan Mambazham
subTitle: Moidukutty Haji returns to his village after taking a third wife, despite his other wives' disapproval. Unbeknownst to him, his young and beautiful new bride, Amina, is secretly in love with Abdu, a bangle seller.

title: Padakkalam
subTitle: Four engineering students battle their professor's supernatural schemes to control the campus, encountering cursed gadgets and bizarre scenarios along the way.

title: Neyyattinkara Gopante Aaraattu
subTitle: An affluent man is called upon to hand over his vast plot of land to the government. However, situations take a turn when he brings the influential Neyyattinkara Gopan into the picture.
